ntroduction: On Ubuntu Linux root is a particular user account. By default, the root user has access to all commands, files, services on an Ubuntu Linux operating system. It is also known as the root account, root user and the superuser. The superuser or root user has root privileges. It is the most privileged account on Ubuntu with complete access to everything. The MS-Windows equivalent of root is the Administrators group or Administrator user. This page shows how to log in as root or superuser on Ubuntu to perform sysadmin related tasks.